	The decision was taken during the council meeting on Thursday. WATCH: De Lille to challenge DA ousting in court It was tabled by Deputy Mayor Ian Nielson in hopes of ensuring effective service delivery. The councillors passed the motion designating all legislative authority away from the Mayor, with 137 votes to 50. Two councillors abstained, while the ANC and EFF rejected the proposal. De Lille will still be able to appoint a mayoral committee. She plans to fight the demotion. eNCA